        <abstract>
            <p>Thanks SC for his interesting account of the state of the colony. SC was wise to settle there where his sons have much better prospects.</p>
            <p>Has finished his book on barnacles [1854]. Royal Medal awarded him chiefly for this work.</p>
            <p>Asks SC whether he has observed any odd imported breeds of poultry, for his work on variation of species.</p>
        </abstract>
